review_reply.reply_text:
Hi,

Basis of any successful treatment is adhering to scheduled appointments.  Motto of our clinic is to provide quality treatment and provide utmost patient satisfaction, but to help us in  achieving this it is required from the patient side to maintain his appointments and visit when scheduled.  As noted, you have given a gap of 7 months which will make any treatment planned fail.

Would like to again like to bring to your notice the cause of the issue.  Any arteficial teeth like bridge or implant can be successful when we have good condition of the gums ( on which these artificial teeth rest).  In case we have poor gum conditions, we have to first treat that issue majorly the gaps and pockets in which the food gets stuck and then apply the bridge back post gum pocket correction. Healthy gums is a fundamental of any arteficial teeth

For the sole reason you were advised to apply ointments and gum paints to solve the issue post gum cleaning and was scheduled appointment after 20 days to get the bridge placed, but you never visited to get it done even after 7 months.  
   
A doctor can schedule visit but it is the duty of patient to return and get the work done and take the treatment to conclusion. That is how any treatment works and its both ways  

Would hope it will help in understanding the cause and importance of schedule and treatment planning for its completion. 

Regards

review_reply.reply_text:
Dear patient,

The tooth was completely decayed and broken and had all roots carious and damaged which was examined by x ray investigation.  The only option for such badly decayed is removal or extraction.  The tooth had sepis and pus discharge and keeping such tooth is also hazardous for adjacent teeth.  We can save tooth by performing root canal treatment but for that the roots need to be in healthy condition and not rotten with some crown structure to support fillings and crowns which was not there in your case.  We only perform legitimate procedures keeping in mind treatment should be successful in future and not few day affair. As relationship between patients and our clinic is long lasting and based on trust, which is the pillar of our practice and motto. Keeping prognosis of procedure as prime is basis of successful treatment and a must.  Hope you understand and if you would have visited clinic few years back and not let it rot for so many years we could have saved the same.  That is why the only option extraction was suggested.

Regards
Team Hsdc
